body:
I have a custom `stubs.php` file declaring a class `WPSEO_Primary_Term` and its methods but it doesn't seem adding that file to the config file makes a difference?
I'm pretty sure I'm missing anything, though. Any help would be hugely appreciated.

Thanks in advance

### psalm.xml
```xml
<psalm>
    ...
    <stubs>
        <file name="stubs.php" />
        <file name="vendor/giacocorsiglia/wordpress-stubs/wordpress-stubs.php" />
    </stubs>
</psalm>
```

### stubs.php
```php
<?php

/** Yoast */
class WPSEO_Primary_Term {
	public function get_primary_term(): int {}
	public function __construct( string $tax_name, int $postid ) {
		_parent( $tax_name, $postid );
	}
}
```

### theme/lib/utils.php
```php
<?php
function bw_get_category( string $tax_name = 'category' ) {
	$post_id = get_the_ID();
	$term = null;
	if ( class_exists( 'WPSEO_Primary_Term' ) ) {
		$yoast  = new WPSEO_Primary_Term( $tax_name, $post_id );
		$cat_id = $yoast->get_primary_term();
		$t = get_term( $cat_id );
		if ( $t instanceof \WP_Term ) {
			$term = $t;
		}
	} else {
		$term = bw_get_terms( $tax_name )[0];
	}
	return $term;
}
```

